@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F4F8
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #FFE6CC

title SD-05 - Polling Voting Flow

actor Visitor
participant Browser
participant Server
participant Router
participant Controller
participant Model
database Database

Visitor -> Browser: 1. Navigate to page with poll\nGET /page-with-poll
activate Browser

Browser -> Server: 2. GET /page-with-poll
activate Server
deactivate Browser

Server -> Router: 3. Route to Polling controller
activate Router
deactivate Server

Router -> Controller: 4. Call index() method
activate Controller
deactivate Router

note right of Controller
    Load polling data:
    - Get active question
    - Get answer options
    - Check if user already voted (session)
end note

Controller -> Model: 5. view_where_ordering_limit('poling',"status='Pertanyaan'",'id_poling','DESC',0,1)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 6. SELECT * FROM poling\nWHERE status = 'Pertanyaan'\nORDER BY id_poling DESC LIMIT 1
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 7. Return polling question
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 8. Return question data
deactivate Model
activate Controller

Controller -> Model: 9. view_where_ordering_limit('poling',"status='Jawaban'",'id_poling','ASC',0,10)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 10. SELECT * FROM poling\nWHERE status = 'Jawaban'\nORDER BY id_poling ASC LIMIT 10
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 11. Return answer options
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 12. Return answer data
deactivate Model
activate Controller

note right of Controller
    Check voting session:
    - Look for 'poling' session variable
    - If exists, user already voted
end note

Controller -> Browser: 13. Render poll in template\n(template().'/template', template().'/content', $data)
activate Browser

Browser -> Visitor: 14. Display poll with options
deactivate Browser

opt User submits vote
    Visitor -> Browser: 15. Select answer and submit\nPOST /polling/vote
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Server: 16. POST /polling/vote\n(answer_id, captcha)
    activate Server
    deactivate Browser

    Server -> Router: 17. Route to Polling controller vote()
    activate Router
    deactivate Server

    Router -> Controller: 18. Call vote() method
    activate Controller
    deactivate Router

    note right of Controller
        Validate submission:
        - Check captcha
        - Verify answer exists
        - Check if user already voted
    end note

    alt Captcha valid and not voted
        note right of Controller
            Process vote:
            - Increment rating for selected answer
            - Set session to prevent double voting
        end note

        Controller -> Model: 19. update('poling', ['rating'=>$rating+1], ['id_poling'=>$answer_id])
        activate Model

        Model -> Database: 20. UPDATE poling SET rating = rating + 1\nWHERE id_poling = $answer_id
        activate Database
        deactivate Model

        Database --> Model: 21. Update successful
        deactivate Database
        activate Model

        Model --> Controller: 22. Return update result
        deactivate Model
        activate Controller

        note right of Controller
            Set voting session:
            - Store 'poling' in session
            - Prevent future votes
        end note

        Controller -> Browser: 23. redirect('main')
        activate Browser

        Browser -> Visitor: 24. Redirect to homepage\n(vote recorded)
        deactivate Browser

    else Invalid captcha or already voted
        Controller -> Browser: 25. redirect('main')
        activate Browser

        Browser -> Visitor: 26. Redirect to homepage\n(vote not recorded)
        deactivate Browser
    end
end

opt User views poll results
    Visitor -> Browser: 27. Click view results\nGET /polling/lihat
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Server: 28. GET /polling/lihat
    activate Server
    deactivate Browser

    Server -> Router: 29. Route to Polling controller lihat()
    activate Router
    deactivate Server

    Router -> Controller: 30. Call lihat() method
    activate Controller
    deactivate Router

    note right of Controller
        Load results data:
        - Get question
        - Get all answers with ratings
        - Calculate percentages
    end note

    Controller -> Model: 31. view_where_ordering_limit('poling',"status='Pertanyaan'",'id_poling','DESC',0,1)
    activate Model

    Model -> Database: 32. SELECT * FROM poling\nWHERE status = 'Pertanyaan'\nORDER BY id_poling DESC LIMIT 1
    activate Database
    deactivate Model

    Database --> Model: 33. Return question
    deactivate Database
    activate Model

    Model --> Controller: 34. Return question
    deactivate Model
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Model: 35. view_where_ordering_limit('poling',"status='Jawaban'",'rating','DESC',0,10)
    activate Model

    Model -> Database: 36. SELECT * FROM poling\nWHERE status = 'Jawaban'\nORDER BY rating DESC LIMIT 10
    activate Database
    deactivate Model

    Database --> Model: 37. Return answers with ratings
    deactivate Database
    activate Model

    Model --> Controller: 38. Return results data
    deactivate Model
    activate Controller

    note right of Controller
        Calculate statistics:
        - Total votes
        - Percentages for each option
        - Sort by rating descending
    end note

    Controller -> Browser: 39. Render results template\n(template().'/template', template().'/lihatpoling', $data)
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Visitor: 40. Display poll results\nwith percentages
    deactivate Browser
end

@enduml
